{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b7cfc37a-0130-44b8-856f-ea3d239afb1d","content":"No files found in the working directory — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**What changes:**\n- Add the `xmlns:vm` namespace import for your ViewModel's namespace.\n- Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `ContentPage` (or any parent element).\n- Your existing `{Binding ...}` expressions stay the same — the compiler now resolves them at build time instead of using reflection at runtime.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, **misspelled or missing properties become build errors**. For example, `{Binding Themee}` will produce:\n\n```\nerror XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\nTo ensure this is fully enforced, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding failures as errors, not warnings -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n## Tips\n\n| Scenario | How to handle |\n|---|---|\n| Binding to a different type mid-tree | Add `x:DataType=\"vm:OtherType\"` on that element |\n| Need to opt out (e.g., `BindingContext` set dynamically) | Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that subtree |\n| Two-way binding (e.g., `FontSize` slider) | `{Binding FontSize, Mode=TwoWay}` — works the same, just compiled |\n\nCompiled bindings give you **build-time safety** and **~8× faster** binding resolution by eliminating runtime reflection.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"17152130-625d-442c-8f96-f8c957a477d0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the directory. The user is asking a general question about how to convert a .NET MAUI page to use compiled bindings. Let me provide guidance based on what they described.\n\nSince there are no actual files, I'll explain the concept and show the code changes needed.","outputTokens":687,"requestId":"1107:834FC:B951EC:D96D52:69FE8508"},"id":"e66a0f29-5b23-4196-85f4-96db5aa3c79f","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:35.063Z","parentId":"60b1cd6d-aeeb-4ddd-afc5-38f2a29dbf30"}
